We're OpenRock

The founder of OpenRock, Jack Lee, is an avid outdoor enthusiast whose life is connected to nature. He also has a great love for music, which has always been an important part of his outdoor experience, whether he's running, cycling, or camping. He tried a variety of in-ear earbuds and bone conduction headphones and found that they each had their shortcomings.

Driven to solve this dilemma, Jack surveyed hundreds of fellow adventurers and discovered a frustrating truth — people were forced to choose between safety, health, and sound quality. Refusing to accept this compromise, he was determined to change that.

In 2018, Jack began developing air-conduction headphones that merged the best of in-ear and bone-conduction technologies while eliminating their flaws. After three years of repeated experiments, his team finally overcame the sound leakage and sound balance problems. In April 2021, OpenRock was officially founded. With its unique open sound field design, outdoor enthusiasts can listen to music while still clearly capturing the sound of the wind and birdsong.

"The purest freedom amplifies the world, never drowns it out." This insistence on the communion of nature and technology has become the origin of OpenRock's deep exploration of air conduction technology.

EcoSoul is a category disrupting consumer products company that is on a journey to democratize the market for eco-friendly home essentials and drive the world’s transition to a more sustainable lifestyle. Our Story
The Organic To Green Group has a deep-rooted connection to the wellness culture, weaving together the realms of service, healing, and beauty. It all began with the first Organic To Green establishment in the serene coastal town of Santa Monica, California. From the outset, our brand and identity have been inspired by the calming and revitalizing ethos of the beachside lifestyle, aiming to introduce this essence of relaxation to the wider American scene. Our journey has been marked by the creation of signature treatments and wellness spas that have garnered acclaim.

Our commitment to excellence has led to the development of award-winning products and a distinctive style that has caught the attention of prestigious publications and platforms such as Allure, Forbes, Allure Best of Beauty, Women's Health Mag Best, Martha Stewart American Made Style Finalist, Refinery 29, WELL+GOOD, Zoe Report, Redbook, New Beauty, Latina, Cosmopolitan, US Weekly, Marie Claire, Huffington Post, E Online, Today Show, QVC Germany, HSE24, Ulta, Fitness, Nylon, Glamour, Shape, Pregnancy Newborn, Today Show, Good Morning America, Real Simple, New Beauty, Better Home and Gardens, Working Mother, Parent and Child, New York, The Doctors, The View, and many more.

Furthermore, Organic to Green takes pride in producing amenities for small businesses and crafting airline amenities specifically designed for first-class lounges and carriers. Our brand has even graced the screens of popular television shows like Today, Good Morning America, HSE Italia, and WVC Germany.

In an exciting evolution, Organic to Green has expanded to Organic To Green Medspa, where we redefine beauty through a lens of modernity and grace. We partnered with Dr. Tristan Bickman, a renowned OBGYN based in Santa Monica, to bring cutting-edge medical expertise to our holistic approach. This collaboration ensures that our clients receive the best of both worlds—traditional wellness wisdom combined with advanced medical insights.

Every aspect of what we do, from our services to product development and the selection of ingredients, is rooted in our mission to bring harmony. We are dedicated to not only providing exceptional experiences and high-quality products but also prioritizing the well-being of our planet.

At Organic To Green, we believe in the power of nature to restore balance and promote a sense of overall wellness. With our unwavering commitment to the well-being of individuals and the planet, we invite you to join us on this transformative journey towards harmony and embrace the beauty of a truly holistic lifestyle.

But what does this mean in practice?
Beautiful - We create showstopping baked goods for our beautiful customers. Whether you choose one of our signature designs or opt for something bespoke, you will receive a cake, brownie, cookie or Coorownie that’s been designed to showcase how beautiful you are.
Loved -  They say love is the greatest gift of all. We agree! We are in the business of creating lovingly handmade luxury baked goods to help our customers celebrate themselves and their loved ones. But this doesn’t happen at the expense of the planet. Sustainability is at the heart of our business. All our packaging is either made from recyclable materials, recyclable or both. Our brownies are presented in tins that double as storage or baking tins and are accompanied with a recipe card for a cake that fits them perfectly. We are also big advocates of self care so our thank you and recipe cards double as adult colouring cards for when you need some time alone to relax and let your creative juices run free.

Unique - All our customers are beautifully unique and this inspires us to create some of the most unique cakes and bakes you’ll find. From our best selling Esmerelda cake to our gilded brownies, which have been voted the best brownies for a glamorous gift by BBC Good Food, you’ll be hard pressed to find designs more unique than ours.

Special - Our customers are special, so we take special care to choose the best ingredients and materials. When you order from Good Cake Day, you can be confident that quality ingredients such as organic and fair trade extracts, free range eggs and butter with at least 80% fat content has been used. We also take food safety very seriously and everyone who works in our kitchen has an up to date, Food Safety Level 2 certificate. We also hold a 5 star kitchen hygiene certificate from the Food Standards Agency.

Human - Fewer words sum up what it means to be human like connection. Our goal is to help our customers connect to their loved ones in a personal and thoughtful way. All orders come with a complimentary handwritten note in a wax sealed gold lined envelope. We call this a BLUSH card. We’ve received feedback from our customers that their loved ones felt special and like royalty when they read their personalised BLUSH cards.

Our mission
Superstratum’s mission is to end building related illness (BRI) by purifying the homes we live in from mycotoxins.
How We Began
Our story
Superstratum was founded with a mission to address the hidden dangers of Building Related Illness (BRI). Our research uncovered a critical missing link: mycotoxins that linger even after mold remediation. Through conversations with medical professionals and those affected, we saw firsthand how deeply mycotoxins impact mental, physical, and spiritual health. What began as curiosity became a commitment to revolutionizing indoor environments. For many on our team, this issue is personal—we’ve experienced its effects in our own lives, which is why we’re dedicated to helping others reclaim healthier spaces.
Our Promise
"You won’t find a team more committed to your family’s health. Our mission is to provide products and solutions that create a healthier home—so you can move beyond merely surviving and start truly living."
Seth Jones
Founder & CEO

About YOELEO Company Overview Company Name: YOELEO SPORTS CO., LIMITED Founded: 2007 Established: 2011 Location: FLAT/RM B3 19/F TUNG LEE COMMERCIAL BUILDING 91-97 JERVOIS STREET SHEUNG WAN HONG KONG CHINA Representative: President Liu Xingpei Business Description: YOELEO is a bicycle manufacturer, with its main products including carbon fiber frame sets, wheel sets, handlebars, and complete bicycles. Story  
In 2011, YOELEO, founded by Leo and his friends who share a common passion for cycling from Canada, the UK, Germany, Italy, and China, is an international company with a rich history rooted in the cycling industry. The story of YOELEO began in early 2007 with the OEM manufacturing of carbon fiber components for overseas bicycle brands. After years of perfecting the technology, we created milestones named after our visionary founder, Leo.  

At our core, we value self-discipline and freedom, which drive us forward and fuel our passion for cycling. We believe that cycling is not just a sport, but a means to push beyond one’s limits, discover inner strength, and achieve greatness. Since our founding, we have cherished these values and delighted our customers with a variety of cycling disciplines designed with a fun and progressive lifestyle in mind.  

Driven by a shared passion for cycling and a commitment to excellence, we continually push boundaries and create innovative cycling-related products that embody our core values of self-discipline and freedom. From road to mountain, triathlon to gravel, we offer a wide range of types and models to enhance the cyclist experience and maximize potential. With a network of distributors spread across the globe, we are dedicated to providing excellent products and services that empower our customers with the strength of self-discipline and freedom. We remain committed to quality, believing that by providing more reliable and stable products, we can contribute to the healthy lifestyles of professional riders and cycling enthusiasts.  

Company History  
2011: YOELEO brand established  
2015: Authorized and utilized in over 110 countries and regions  
Sponsored IVAN JIANG for a 125-day, 6500 km cycling challenge across America  
2016: Sponsored the Italian team "CYKELN," setting the fastest record at Red Hook Crit Milano  
2017: All road bike wheels received UCI certification  
Established a European warehouse in Germany and began servicing EU users  
2019: YOELEO in Japan/China/Australia/Indonesia

About Us
Groove Calligraphy was born in a time of crisis, out of a parent's need, when all of us have suddenly found ourselves trying to adapt to the unknown and new living conditions, new goals, new ways of education, predominantly at home. In our hands stands the education of the next generation. This set of manuals is the answer we've devised to a question that has risen:

How can I help my child make their first steps into the world of learning, given that the world we know is changing drastically?

We wholeheartedly stand by our products and can't wait for you to feel the difference they make!

Order your Groove Calligraphy , risk-free! We will not disappoint!

Our wish is for parent-child learning to become a fun, interactive, bond-creating experience, turning math into easy number play, learning to write into a smooth transition from drawing.

As parents there's nothing we wish more than seeing our little ones succeeding and thriving, we know home-schooling can be a challenging task. This is how we ended up developing Groove Calligraphy... with the goal of building a ladder that us parents will use when helping our children climb the mountain of knowledge, making sure they get the best start they can get, seeing them enjoy the journey, and smiling at the challenges.

Children’s experience with writing and creating texts is an important avenue for self-expression in early childhood. These experiences also support precursors to their later reading and writing development.

Our extensive research allowed us to create learning experiences that are responsive, intentional, and catering to the learning needs of children. And we have put them all together in our Groove Calligraphy.You'll be amazed by how efficient and fun they are for your beloved.

ABOUT US

FOUNDING MISSION
To improve human, ecological and economic health by increasing the cultivation and consumption of plant diversity.

From Dr. Cowan: The philosophy behind our company is simple and emerges from my almost 40 years of studying food and nutrition and from working with my patients.

My conception of a healthy diet is one that includes a liberal amount of healthy fats (grass-fed butter or ghee, coconut oil, olive oil) and proteins (wild fish, grass-fed land animals, pastured poultry and eggs) to build a healthy body, make hormones (fats), nourish our immune systems (fats and proteins) and obtain calories for energy (fats). These two categories of food should make up the bulk of most people's diets.

The plants have a different purpose. We eat grains (for those that tolerate them) as an energy food, and fruits and vegetables for their concentrated vitamins, minerals and varied phytochemicals, which are so important for human health. Unlike animals, plants are stationary and use chemistry to defend themselves against predators and disease. These chemicals also provide vitamins, antioxidants and other healing elements for humans.

In fact, taking our lead from healthy traditional peoples, we should strive to eat at least 10 to 12 different plants a day: some roots (carrots, beets), some stems (celery, Brussels sprouts), some leaves (kale, chard), and some fruits and flowers (tomatoes, zucchini). Eating different plant parts and colors is the surest way to avail ourselves of all the nutrients plants have to offer.

The problem is, even for someone with a large garden, it's challenging, if not practically impossible, to eat even five plants a day. Dr. Cowan's Garden powders were created to address this problem.

Our Story

Introducing the yet unknown treasures in Japan to the world.

The workmanship of masters, nurtured through the culture and traditions of Japan, has been passed down for hundreds of years, and fine works created with the passion of craftsmen and the traditional skills of the masters continue to remain unknown at locations throughout the country.

Japanese craftsmanship has been attracting people throughout the world, and it offers a wealth of potential for enriching our daily lives. Yet a lot of these gems remain unknown, not only to the outside world but within Japan as well.

We seek to go beyond the barriers of culture and have people throughout the world discover and experience the true values and the potential of genuine work created by Japanese masters.

To do that, we are setting up a venue to connect Japan and the world, to get many people in the global community involved in the coming years, decades, and centuries as we deliver surprise, elation, and happiness while boosting the value of traditional Japanese culture and master craftsmanship and promoting their further advancement. For that purpose, we have launched Master Craftsmanship, a venue to make such encounters happen.

But there are limits to what we can do on our own. The more people who become involved, the greater the scope of potential will be. We are looking at spending years and decades to bring Japan and the global community together and to get many people in the world involved so we may continue to expand new possibilities.

Our Story – From Tech to TokuDeals
What if your side project became your true calling?

Hi, I’m Lara! I used to work full-time as an IT professional here in Japan. But deep down, I always had the heart of an entrepreneur—and a love for sharing Japan’s most exciting and meaningful finds with people around the world.

The Sandbox That Sparked a Dream
TokuDeals started in 2017 as a personal sandbox project—a way for me to learn how to build an online business in Japan. I began with dropshipping, then moved on to selling authentic products made in Japan. But everything changed in 2019, when I posted a photo of a Sanrio Characters Hide and Seek gachapon. That one post caught the attention of the Hello Kitty collectors community —and it lit a spark I couldn’t ignore. That was the bridge that connected me with the community. 

In 2020, during the pandemic, I started live selling Hello Kitty items from home—sometimes with my kids helping behind the scenes. A few months later, I took a big step and did my very first live shopping event inside a Sanrio Gift Gate store.

That’s when I truly felt it: this was more than just a business. It was a community in the making.

What began as a hobby soon became a growing community, and in 2022, I took the leap and became a full-time entrepreneur.

 More Than a Shop—It’s a Community
TokuDeals is more than just kawaii items or exclusive merch. It’s a community built on trust, shared interests, and the fun of shopping together. Whether it’s Sanrio plushies, Japanese snacks, beauty products, anime merch, or something unique you found online—we’re here to help you get it from Japan, packed with love and shipped with care.

Every order we prepare is for someone we consider a friend. Every live show we host is a way to hang out with people who love the same things. We’re proud of the family that’s grown around this brand—and we hope you feel it too

ABOUT US
OUR STORY BEGINS IN 2012 IN HACKNEY, EAST LONDON
We started from scratch. That is why we know that there is no greater victory than looking back and seeing how far you have come.
We are proud that TCA is an organic journey driven by ambition, perseverance, and a strong desire to offer high-quality sportswear that is accessible to all those who love sport just as much as we do. TCA business took off after the launch of a collection of technical compression sportswear, still one of our best-sellers.
We designed and developed our collection for everyday athletes. For those who love running in the park before going to work, playing football with friends, wearing boxing gloves or taking a yoga class. For all types of indoor and outdoor activities.


OPPORTUNITIES & GROWTH
After our compression sportswear, we introduced the Elite Tech Short, the first technical training tees and, after a long period of development, we launched our first women’s style.
Our approach is different: we know that there are no shortcuts to achieving a personal goal! For this reason, we dedicated time and consistency to create a high-quality fabric, that can withstand every workout and last over time. As a result, we launched our Supreme Legging in 2014 and sold 11,000 pairs in the first 12 months.
LIKE AN ATHLETE WHO WANTS TO ACHIEVE A GOAL, WE WORKED DAY AFTER DAY, TO IMPROVE OUR SPORTSWEAR AND DESIGN NEW PRODUCTS.

EVERYDAY HEROES
With urban design and a little cheeky attitude, we support more than a thousand women, men, and kids who train with us. They are our everyday heroes. Despite their busy lives, they manage to carve out time for sports, to fulfill a dream, and feel better.
Without them, we wouldn’t have written our story.

About Us
Planet Desert is a family-owned retail nursery based in Southern California. We are dedicated to growing a wide variety of cacti and succulents and are constantly adding, developing, and creating more products. We offer the best quality plants at the best prices possible. After all, we've been in the business for years!


I developed a passion for plants way back in my early twenties. I grew up in the outskirts of Mexico City, surrounded by nature. My family owned a big piece of land which was divided between my parents, my brothers, my sister, and me. We each had our own house and shared common areas with a pool, a huge garden, and some undeveloped land. Eventually, my brothers and I built a greenhouse and launched a business selling poinsettias. That's when it all started.

I left the poinsettia business to my brother and worked some other jobs (not plant related). But, once you work with plants, soil, flowers, seeds, etc. there's no going back. I felt a yearning and I missed the smell of damp soil and watching how a few seeds can turn into a beautiful shrub, especially when nurtured with just the right amount of water and light! Gardening is truly therapeutic. I’m sure a lot of you will agree with me when I say that plants become part of the family, just like pets.

Eighteen years ago my wife, my two beautiful daughters, and I moved to California. We packed up and left Mexico with no specific plan. A true improvisation leading to a life project. Mendocino offered excellent conditions to go back to the plant business. Soon enough, I was experimenting with cacti and succulents and Planet Desert was born.

Three years later, we moved down South, to beautiful Fallbrook, California. Here, the Mediterranean weather is just what our cacti and succulents (and we) needed.

Not only are we a nursery that offers beautiful and unique succulent and cactus plants, but we also deliver! We have perfected the art of shipping our gorgeous plants across the country, allowing you to enjoy a new plant, no matter where you are. While it may seem strange to have a plant shipped to you, we ensure that your new plant will arrive in perfect condition.

Be sure to shop through our collection of succulents and cacti, read up on care instructions, and order your favorite plant today! Contact us with any questions you may have.

 Mark, Citlali, Kiara and Ana

YOU FEELING GOOD– IT’S OUR MISSION
HUM’s mission is to help you find your confidence and feel good in your skin and body.
We make this promise to you by making your health and wellness our number one priority. For us, it’s about always bringing you unique, ultra-targeted products formulated with verified clean ingredients and clinically tested actives to help you reach your wellness goals. We commit to providing you support from a personal RD, too. And, the wellness of our planet matters, so all of our packaging is sustainable and made from upcycled materials such as prevented ocean plastic. Every wellness journey is unique and we are committed to yours–whatever that looks like. We’re clean, clinical and made for you.

Feel Good, Life Changing Science
From skin struggle to personal success–that’s the HUM way.

Our co-founder is no stranger to dealing with problematic skin. After years of adult acne and trying topical solutions and prescription drugs that only worked temporarily, Walter had an instinct that his digestion could be the culprit. So, he approached a forward-thinking nutritionist who understood the importance of gut health in relation to skin health.

This is where everything changed and the idea for HUM was born. The obsession for researching ways to address concerns at the core and through nutrition grew, as did the desire to help people live as their best, healthiest selves. HUM hired scientists, began to explore people’s diverse issues and find ways to solve for those individual struggles by developing nutritional solutions that target very specific skin, hair, body and mood needs.

Our commitment to finding what’s right for you doesn’t end with active ingredients that have demonstrated–in clinical trials–to produce results. At HUM, we are all consumers and as such, we are obsessed with quality. From potent clinically tested actives to help you achieve your wellness goals, to finding the best suppliers for ingredients to triple testing and formulating without unnecessary widely used fillers that may make a pill brighter or cheaper to produce.

We made it our mission to make you feel good from the inside out and approach our products as a consumer first, creating clean verified, quality products that could be trusted to do what they promised and took into account future generations and the future of our planet with conscious prevented ocean plastic packaging.

Over the years, HUM has evolved with more research, products dedicated to women’s health–at every stage in her life, more innovation and a strong, supportive community. Because of our genuine passion for problem solving, HUM has become a wellness pioneer with an optimistic approach to struggles and a promise to feel good, life changing science delivered right to your doorstep.

Welcome to Hesacore
Beyond the Ordinary Grip
We believe in pushing the boundaries of innovation to enhance the performance and comfort of racket athletes worldwide.

THE GRIP
The Science Behind Hesacore
Hesacore grip technology, developed through extensive research, addresses common issues for racket sports enthusiasts. Our biomechanically designed hexagonal pattern conforms to the hand's natural contours, reducing harmful vibrations.

Engineered to enhance protection, comfort, grip, and performance.

Traditional 8-edged handles misalign with hand anatomy, lacking lateral support and finger alignment, especially for modern spin techniques. Proper use of the bottom three fingers, with the little finger as the fulcrum, is crucial. The index and thumb aid in controlling and speeding up racket head rotation.
Hesacore's hexagonal pattern enhances friction, allowing a looser grip and preventing slipping. This relaxation extends to the wrist and forearm, resulting in smoother, more powerful shots.

About Us
HowCork is a family-operated online store dedicated to promoting environmental stewardship in the world of fashion. We're passionate about protecting nature, animals, and human health alike through the use of cork in place of textiles such as animal leather or synthetic PU leather. We source vegan, handmade, quality cork products from numerous small, ethical brands and bring them all to one virtual space. Our goal is to help to keep the tradition of cork harvesting alive in the Mediterranean and spread the culture of cork to North America. We believe that you don't have to sacrifice anything in terms of personal style in order to live and shop in a way that respects the planet.
Why We Love Cork
Cork is truly a masterpiece of nature, with unique characteristics that allow it to hold up for years and years of use. From bark to bag, cork does not pollute or create waste throughout its entire lifecycle. We believe that cruelty is not a fashion statement, and choosing cork is actively creating a healthier and more peaceful world for future generations. We want to ensure that the cork forests of the Mediterranean continue to thrive, as cork oaks are what keep the entire Mediterranean basin from becoming a desert. These forests are second only to the Amazon rainforest in terms of biodiversity.

Surprisingly, the best way to care for the cork oak forests is to harvest and use cork bark! The process of harvesting cork uses ancient techniques and hand-tools to remove just the bark without harming the tree. It allows the cork oak trees to become more robust and have a longer lifespan, while amplifying their ability to release oxygen and absorb carbon dioxide from the atmosphere. Cork has an integral role to play in the sustainable fashion movement - and we're here to help bring it into the spotlight. Our store is based in South Florida, where we keep all of our products in stock and ship with no plastic and minimal packaging.

My Journey: Starting Matt-Hat Jerky at Age 11

My name is Matthew Kuplack, and I started Matt-Hat Jerky when I was 11 years old
The Matt-Hat Jerky story began long before I was born. My Grandpa Kuplack was making some amazing jerky when my Dad was little. He did not sell it, but he gave it to everyone he liked.

(If you were one of those people, consider yourself lucky and if you knew him, but didn’t get any jerky, well, now you know why.)

Grandpa gave his secret recipe to many people and he told them “Shhh…I am only giving this recipe to you”. After Grandpa died in 2013 my dad compared the “Secret Recipe” he was given with the “Secret Recipe” many others were given only to find out that no one had been given the real secret recipe at all!

"Good old Grandpa! He is funny even now! I watched my Dad make some pretty good jerky trying to duplicate Grandpa’s. When I decided that I would like to start a business, making a Jerky business just made sense because I had helped my Dad make batches of jerky for so long. I started changing my Dad’s recipes around for a while until finally I had zeroed in on the flavor that I liked most. It is savory, chewy and delicious with just a little kick of heat. My sisters Kayla and Katrina (Twins – 3 years older than me) agreed to help with the business and we started making batches and selling them around the neighborhood and to the teachers and students at school. Since then this business has grown like crazy with reviews from chef icons Guy Fieri and Andrew Zimmern! Opening a store and selling more jerky than I ever thought possible is a lot to think about but it's all good! Happy Chewing!"
Matt

Say Hi!
“As an artist, high-quality inks are some of the most fierce tools in my arsenal of artistic endeavors. Almost every medium I work in I find myself reaching for a bottle of ink. As I was doing that, I found most companies I was buying from sold too small of bottles. They were gone in a blink! We’ve fixed that.”

Tiffani Buteau

Hailing from beautiful and quaint Olalla, Washington on the Puget Sound, T-Rex Inks was founded by myself, resin artist Tiffani Buteau, and my husband Stephen. I am the T, and he is the Rex. Together, we found a way to bring to the market what we couldn’t find on the market, affordable, high-quality inks that have robust color and come in a hefty-sized pack. We have always been of the mind that if you can’t find it, make it! After years of working with the material, I understood very well what I would want ideally, so we set about sourcing it and designing the pack. After vigorous testing of the prototypes, we are very happy to bring T-Rex Alcohol Inks to the world!

About us
WHERE IT BEGAN
Hey, I'm Kerry and I'm a stationery addict!

It all started in 2018 whilst putting together a few back to school supplies that matched each of my children's personalities, the idea was born after lots of my childrens classmates asked me to make more, so a Facebook page was made and a stall was requested at the upcoming summer fete. I had no idea at the time that 6 months later I would be quitting my nursery job and selling worldwide on Etsy! 

WHERE WE ARE NOW
The turning point came when I incorporated journal supplies to my little shop and sales boomed! Being a part of such an incredibly talented community spurred me on to take the plunge and create Scribblet Stationery’s website. Since then i've worked with so many amazing creators and branched out to all corners of the world and now supplying your favourite stationery items from places such as New York, Japan & Korea.

My aim is to inspire your craft even further and hope to see you along the way, the ever expanding community can be followed at @scribbletstationery where I post behind the scenes on this whole journey.

About Us Welcome to Premier Bidets, where our journey into the world of bidets began with a spark of inspiration during a five-week adventure in Thailand back in 2013.   Founded by John Grant and his wife Giuliana, our love for bidets blossomed in the most unexpected of places, leading us to create a company that embodies more than just selling bidet products; it's about sharing a transformative experience.  Our Story Our adventure started on a bucket list trip to Asia, where we first encountered the marvel of Japanese toilets and bidets. This experience in a Narita, Japan airport, followed by the ubiquitous use of "bum guns" in Thailand, changed our perspective on personal hygiene.   The cleanliness and comfort provided by bidets were unlike anything we had experienced before, and by the time we returned home to the U.S., we knew something was missing in our daily lives.  Determined to recreate that level of hygiene and comfort, we embarked on a mission to find the perfect bidet solutions for our home.  This quest led to the birth of Premier Bidets, a family-owned and operated business based in Martinez, CA, dedicated to bringing the same level of cleanliness and luxury to bathrooms across America.  Since opening our (virtual) doors, we’ve shipped over 5,000 orders and nearly $10 million worth of luxury bathroom products to homes and businesses across the U.S.  Along the way, we’ve built a reputation that we’re proud of—hundreds of 5-star reviews from customers who appreciate not just the products, but the service, expertise, and support that come with them.  Today, Premier Bidets is trusted by homeowners, interior designers, hotels, and short‑term rental hosts who want to elevate the bathroom experience.  And this is just the beginning.  Our Mission Looking ahead, we’re focused on expanding our product offerings, improving our customer experience, and leading the way as bidets become a mainstream part of American life.  Our goal is simple: make luxury bathroom upgrades easy, accessible, and enjoyable for everyone.  Why Choose Us? Expertise and Passion: Our team is not only knowledgeable about our products but also passionate about the benefits that bidets provide. We're here to answer your questions and help you find the perfect bidet solution for your home or business.  Quality and Affordability: As an online retailer, we work directly with manufacturers to offer premium bidet products at the most competitive prices. Our low price match policy ensures you always get the best deal.  Customer Care: Exceptional customer service is at the heart of what we do. We're committed to transparency, honesty, and integrity in all our business practices. Our Better Business Bureau accreditation is a testament to our commitment to excellence. Join Our Journey From our first encounter with a Japanese toilet in Narita to starting the business, our journey has been one of discovery, cleanliness, and comfort.  Let us help you find the perfect bidet seat, bum gun, or Japanese toilet to upgrade your bathroom experience drastically.  At Premier Bidets, we're a community of enthusiasts dedicated to changing the way you think about bathroom hygiene.  Join us on this journey and experience the difference for yourself!

About LensPen: Your Go-To Camera and Lens Cleaning Kit Provider
Why LensPen?

Years ago many people cleaned mirrors or window panes with newspaper…why did this work so well?

Newspaper is covered with printing ink
Printing ink is made with a carbon compound
Carbon molecules have a unique ability to absorb huge amounts of oils and contaminants
The cleaning tip of LensPen is impregnated with a unique carbon compound. THE CARBON DOES THE CLEANING!
LensPen Features:

SAFE – Use on all optical lenses, LCD, plasma and glass surfaces
EFFECTIVE – Nothing removes oily fingerprints and dust better than a LensPen!
CONVENIENT – Compact size, no liquids, easy to use!
CUSTOM DESIGN – Unique designs, colors, and shapes for different applications!
LONG LIFE – Cannot dry out, unaffected by temperature, over 500 cleanings each!
Corporate Information
Parkside Optical Inc. (“Parkside”) is a wholly-owned subsidiary of International Parkside Products Inc, a Vancouver-based public company listed on the TSX Venture Exchange in Canada. Since 1992 Parkside has been involved in the design, production, and marketing of products to clean fingerprints on high-quality optical and screen products including cameras, filters, binoculars, scopes, computers, digital picture frames, and most recently iPads, tablet computers, iPhones and Android Phones.

Parkside products make use of a unique carbon cleaning compound for which it has held various patents. New patents have been applied for as the Company expands the range of applications for its fingerprint cleaning technology. Parkside has already registered various trademarks around the world and the Company has been registering trademarks both for new products and in new countries. OUR STORY
Here at North and South Jewelry, we truly believe that fine jewelry should be accessible to everyone from all walks of life, regardless of their financial status.

Our Collection
Designed to enhance the natural beauty and personal style of every woman. We understand individual preferences and every piece is crafted with that in mind.

Our Mission
To deliver quality, high-end fine jewelry at remarkably affordable prices. Achieved by implementing cost-effective practices. We will make beautiful jewelry accessible to all without compromising on quality.

Our Passion
Since 1988, we have been redefining the boundaries of luxury. We believe that beauty knows no bounds, and the joy of owning fine jewelry is a privilege enjoyed by all. Affordable elegance is not just a dream but a tangible reality for all.

Our journey began in 1985, when a young apprentice jeweler in the bustling jewelry scene of Los Angeles discovered his passion for creating beautiful hand-crafted fine jewelry. In 1988, he took a leap of faith and opened the doors to North and South Jewelry in Fullerton, CA, with the primary objective of sharing his collection of beautiful hand-crafted jewelry.

The creation of northandsouthjewelry
However, it was not until the devastating 1990s stock crash in the USA that his perspective underwent a profound transformation. Witnessing the aftermath of financial turmoil and the struggles faced by people from all walks of life, we realized the stark divide between the privileged and the rest. The notion struck him hard—why should fine jewelry be exclusive to the wealthy?

With this newfound understanding, we continue to strive to reshape jewelry as a wealth symbol, to a powerful representation of love, commitment, and individuality.

OUR STORY
We are India's new recognized Start-up tea brand involved in bringing a change in how people drink their tea and glorifying the benefits of tea. Teaology is healthy, sophisticated and luxurious tea brand, all at the same time while keeping our roots intact by empowering farmers of single estate farms. Our exquisite range includes organic loose leaf teas along with beautiful flowers and herbs with the aim to provide healthy, natural and invigorating teas.

Despite being an increasingly saturated market, there is a lack of education and knowledge regarding teas, and that's where we come in. A luxury brand that not only provides an extensive collection of the highest quality of premium loose leaf teas but also seeks to revolutionize the tea industry to deliver an extraordinary and unparalleled tea experience.

We use the finest selections of hand-picked tea leaves of the Camellia Sinensis plant which are nurtured by the expertise of purist farmers who pluck with great precision just for you! All our tea blends from Blue Masala Tea to Green Wellness Tea, all use fresh, natural & organic  tea, whole flowers and herbs. We take pride that we source from all around the world and work with single estate farmers. 

Our sustainability promise and our embryonic passion of tea is the driving force behind this brand. No matter the season, our teas can be served as hot and cold brews. Its benefits go far beyond its exquisite colour and flavour. Our teas, filled with herbs and flowers, are packed with vitamins and antioxidants that are great for cleansing the body of toxins and strengthening our immune system.

WHY LOOSE LEAF TEAS? 
 

We truly believe that tea food pairing is becoming the new alchemy, as the right tea with the right food can unlock not only their own flavours to their full potential – but even release a third flavour. Pairing our teas with food is the perfect way to enhance the taste of a dish as well as the drink itself.

At Teaology, loose leaf teas are preferred due to its rich and smooth flavour as they release less tannins, as compared to finely grounded teas that contain a mixture of teas rather than a pure tea itself. As a result of which, our teas can be consistently enjoyed over a period time without any change in its flavour nor aroma! 

OUR FOUNDERS
 

Sahil Chaplot : A qualified pharmacist with a degree in advertising, he has rich experience in health and food industry from India and New Zealand. He is passionate about teas and has an innate curiosity to develop new combinations and blends of teas, herbs, flowers and fruits. His mind is always busy in developing new products which would be empowering people for their health and lifestyle. He takes care of over all operations, marketing and new product development.

Shraddha Khinvasara : A lawyer by profession and having worked in India and New Zealand at various levels, she is passionate about green teas and just loves any form or combination of green teas. She drinks about 4 cups of green tea a day. Her personal favourite is Teaology Rejuvenating Tulsi Green Tea. She takes care of all the legal things and keeps the brand up and running by being the backbone of the company.

About us: Stefan, Melanie, and I are deeply committed to waste prevention and environmental protection. Therefore, we strive to maintain a sustainable lifestyle. It's important to us that this doesn't restrict our freedom or make us miss out on the joys of life. Therefore, we use products whose consumption leaves a small ecological footprint. In 2020, we founded PURE SOUL to give everyone the opportunity to contribute positively to environmental protection. With our vegan deodorant creams, we want to support you on your path to a sustainable life. The handmade deodorants from our factory contain no plastic and are produced without animal ingredients and, of course, without animal testing. "Every step in the right direction counts. No matter how small." Another goal is to give you a wonderful start to every day. With the various aromas of our deodorant creams, you'll be enchanted every day. Only a happy person can spread happiness into the world. That's why we tell you every day what a great person you are. Because you're worth it! We place particular emphasis on high-quality ingredients in our homemade deodorants. That's why we use raw materials from organic farming – 100 percent plastic-free and vegan. Finding the best quality essential oils isn't always easy. It would be much easier to use perfumes or nature-identical aromas. However, these often cause allergies, so they don't even make it into the tin. Our vegan deodorant creams are therefore also suitable for allergy sufferers and people with sensitive skin. Only the very best for you and our planet. That's why we pay attention to sustainable packaging and the best natural raw materials. By using lightweight tins, we reduce weight and volume and avoid up to 77% CO2 emissions throughout the entire supply chain. Forests, beaches, and oceans are drowning in garbage. Our Story
It’s a family business
It was the 1970s in Bielefeld, Germany. A hunter sought to have handmade leather collars for his greyhounds, so he came to Rolf Trautwein and asked if he could make them. A master saddle maker and a dog owner himself, Rolf was known for his exceptional leather-craftsmanship. He crafted outstanding collars from premium materials for the hunter’s greyhounds. While working on the project, Rolf recognized his aspiration to create leather products with the best possible comfort and functionality for dogs. Impressed by the perfection of the hand-crafted collars, the hunter gifted Rolf a greyhound puppy from his dogs’ offspring. In 1980, at the age of 36, Rolf Trautwein realized his dream by establishing a company to produce high-quality accessories for dogs. His greyhound would later become the symbol of his today’s world-renowned high-end pet brand, HUNTER.

The online store www.hunterpetshop.ca, Hunter Pet Shop Facebook page, and hunterpetshop.ca Instagram page are owned and operated by a privately owned Canadian company Hunter Pet Shop based in the Province of Ontario, Canada. As an official partner of HUNTER, we can offer you online access to all products, new additions and exclusive offers from the HUNTER brand, shipped directly from Canada. The quality of HUNTER products is self-evident. It is a part of the company's philosophy to guarantee this quality and continually improve it. At HUNTER, quality begins with the purchasing of raw materials, continues during processing, and ends with the presentation of the products. We at Hunter Pet Shop trust the products and the good work done by HUNTER and we are proud to be a part of the HUNTER family and successful brand history

ABOUT US
How did we start
Ms. Jineer, one of the co-founders of the company is a Yoga fan. When she was working out about 10 years ago, she hardly found a suitable yoga kit for different level yogis. She experienced several brands' products but did not find a good fit. Hence, the fellows who had the same goal gathered and established Heathyoga aims to provide professional, diversified, affordable, and high-quality yoga gear for yogis.

In the beginning, the team based on their previous experiences to design and launch a collection quickly. The result was not as expected since the collection was lack of market research, that it failed to meet the market's needs, and hard to differentiate from competitive brands.  

Bear the lesson in mind, Jineer asked the team to analyze the market data before kick-off the new product line. Customer-centric was the core value of Heathyoga, requested by Jineer. By studying the market, they discovered that yogis required not only pants but also functional leggings.

Can workout leggings have pockets? How do pants shape the curve? How to improve the feeling when sweating? Would it be suitable to wear the leggings for multiple occasions?

Of course! Heathyoga aims to be the perfect partner with yogis in the workout journey.  Jineer tested the cloth continuously until the one which is moisture-wicking, non-see-through, and 4 ways stretched was found. Meanwhile, the R&D team revised the design several times that finally confirmed yoga pants with both sides and an inner waistband pocket. This functional design can have yogis hands-free from workouts. For better tummy control, high-waisted pants were considered by designers.

After months of hard work, HY21 legging of Heathyoga launched. It was rated as one of the best sellers of Heathyoga and became a classic type of brand.

During the decade, Heathyoga never stops its steps for pursuing progress. And it would be forever to be customer-centric and the best partner for yogis.

Welcome to Forever Written
We are so glad that you are here. We are Ken and Camilla Simone, founders of Forever Written. We are thrilled to welcome you to your new home for meaningful, beautiful, and faith-filled wall art that adds a touch of inspiration to your space. We are a family on a mission to bring you products that help you create a Christ-centered home.

At Forever Written, we believe the Word of God doesn’t just belong on your bookshelf—it belongs on your walls, woven into your everyday life, and written on the hearts of your family.

What started as a personal journey to overcome fear through Scripture has grown into a collection of handcrafted wall art designed to draw hearts heavenward. Inspired by timeless design and anchored in the truth of God's Word, every piece we create is made to speak peace, inspire worship, and quietly remind your household of who God is.


Our Story
It started with a season of fear—and a verse taped to the wall.

As a teenager, I Camilla, battled deep anxiety. I needed something solid to cling to, something unshakable. That’s when I began putting Scripture on my walls. Not for decoration, but survival.

One of the first verses I ever hung was:

“For God hath not given us the spirit of fear; but of power, and of love, and of a sound mind.”
— 2 Timothy 1:7 (KJV)

That simple verse calmed my heart every time I read it. The more I surrounded myself with God’s promises, the more peace I experienced. I didn’t know it then, but I was living out Deuteronomy 6—writing His words on the doorposts of my home and heart.

Years later, after stepping away from a career to stay home and raise our children, that same passage changed the way I viewed our house. It wasn’t just a place to live—it was a place to worship. To disciple. To help shape little hearts for God’s Kingdom.

I remembered how the Word had transformed me, and I longed for our kids to grow up surrounded by that same unshakable truth. Not just hearing it on Sundays, but seeing it daily—on the walls where they ate breakfast, played, prayed, and grew.

But finding Scripture-based wall art that was both biblically sound and beautifully made proved difficult. Then one day, while washing dishes, the Holy Spirit nudged my heart:

If you can’t find it, create it. And make it available to others.

And so, Forever Written was born.

A small seed of obedience. A passion for God’s Word. And a desire to help other families see and remember His promises every day.

Why We Do What We Do

Our homes are sacred spaces. And we believe that what we place in them—on
the walls, in the atmosphere—should nourish the soul.

Our Hope for You

That your walls will echo the Word of God. That your children will grow up surrounded by His promises. That your home will become a place of peace, praise, and purposeful beauty. Because His promises aren’t just meant to be heard… they’re meant to be seen, remembered, and lived.

Forever Written. Timeless Truth, Beautifully Displayed.

OUR MISSION
At Custom Dealer Solutions, our mission is to empower dealerships, detail shops, and businesses across industries with innovative, professional-grade cleaning solutions and programs that drive efficiency, enhance profitability, and deliver exceptional results. As a family-owned and operated company, we are dedicated to building lasting partnerships by offering unmatched service, cutting-edge products, and tailored solutions that help our customers streamline operations, reduce costs, and achieve their goals.
OUR STORY
Custom Dealer Solutions (CDS) is a family-owned and operated company founded in 2018 with a mission to provide professional-grade cleaning and appearance solutions to dealerships, detail shops, and businesses nationwide. What began as a passion for helping businesses streamline operations has grown into a trusted partner for industries such as automotive, marine, RV, transportation, municipalities, janitorial, and more.

Based in Omaha, Nebraska, CDS has earned a reputation for delivering results through high-quality products, exceptional service, and innovative programs tailored to meet the unique needs of each client. We believe in building lasting partnerships with our customers, offering the tools and expertise to help them succeed while staying true to our family values of integrity and commitment.



OUR APPROACH
At CDS, we do more than provide cleaning and appearance products—we partner with our customers to streamline their operations and achieve their goals. Our professional-grade chemical solutions are developed by experienced chemists and backed by hands-on training to ensure your team can use them efficiently and effectively.

To simplify your operations, we’ve built a fully customizable e-commerce platform that makes it easy to order products, manage costs, and restrict access to specific items based on employee roles. This solution is perfect for dealership groups, franchises, and service centers looking to improve efficiency and control expenses.

Beyond vehicle reconditioning, our versatile products tackle cleaning challenges across various industries, from degreasers and enzymatic cleaners to ceramic coatings and solutions for cleaning concrete or porta potties—excluding food-safe applications. We also collaborate with over 30 trusted vendors, allowing us to consolidate your supply chain and reduce the complexity of managing multiple suppliers.

About Us

Our Mission
To improve lives and strengthen families – and we happen to accomplish this
through Hardware. We strive to make our online store easier to use and more
informative to save you time and money.


Our Story
HardwareX Supply was founded by two Kevins in 2017. Their passion for building and remodeling their homes brought them together. At the time, hardware stores were not much of a presence online as it is today. To get their hardware supplies for a weekend project, they had to drive to many different hardware stores to get the supplies they need. After many trips to different hardware stores, they realized they wasted valuable time that could have been spent working on their projects. Sometimes they would spend more time locating the supplies than completing the project itself. They came up with a solution to their problem and created HardwareX Supply.

HardwareX Supply was established to distribute only quality and affordable hardware supplies. Consumers and businesses can plan their projects and can conveniently order their hardware supplies from the comfort of their home or office. Since founded, HardwareX Supply has grown to become one of the leading online hardware supply retailers. They have an extensive list of reputable companies of over 50 different brands and over 1000 products in their online catalog. Their commitment to providing the best possible overall shopping experience is what separates them from their competitors.

OUR JOURNEY SO FAR THE INSPIRATION BEHIND MY3DSELFIE My3DSelfie was born from a deeply emotional experience. In 2010, our founder, Harsha P. Deka, faced the heartbreaking loss of his best friend. Stricken with grief, Harsha sought to create a 3D model of his friend as a keepsake for the family. He approached numerous 3D agencies and animation studios, but none could transform a photograph into a 3D model due to the technological limitations of the time. Disheartened, Harsha shelved the project until a chance encounter with a 3D scanner reignited his vision. Observing people being scanned and receiving 3D-printed figurines, he saw potential but also flaws in the business model. When he inquired about creating 3D models from photographs, the answer was no. This sparked his determination to innovate. Harsha's relentless research led to the founding of My3DSelfie, pioneering the commercialization of 3D-printed figurines from images and creating a new market category.

About CTL

Your Adventure Starts Here!
Bike touring is more than just a sport - it's an exhilarating lifestyle that invites you to embrace the wonders of the world and embark on unforgettable adventures. Whether you're a beginner or a seasoned cyclist, our comprehensive "Bike Touring 101" guide will help you understand the thrilling world of bike touring and bikepacking.

At The Cycle Touring Life (a subsidiary of FREEDOM SPORTING GOODS COMPANY LTD.), we're passionate about exploring the globe on two wheels. With locations and warehouses in both Nova Scotia and Toronto, Canada, our team of experienced cyclists has traveled across Canada, the USA, South America, Europe, Asia, and beyond, learning invaluable lessons along the way. We're here to support, encourage, and equip you with everything you need for your bike touring journey.

Cyclists of all levels can experience the thrill of bike touring, whether it's a short one-day trip or an extended weekend getaway. For the truly adventurous, embarking on a multi-day, week, or even year-long tour offers the ultimate biking experience, complete with camping under the stars and immersing oneself in the journey.

Of course, bike touring requires careful planning, a bit of physical preparation, and the know-how to navigate various terrains and regions. At The Cycle Touring Life, we understand your enthusiasm for exploration, from leisurely rides through the countryside to wild camping, stargazing, and conquering challenging summits. Our mission is to help you create lasting memories with every pedal.

To fully enjoy your bike tour, it's crucial to have the right gear. While some items may not seem essential now, they could prove invaluable during your adventure. Our extensive product range ensures that you're well-prepared for your journey, no matter the destination.

We're more than just a store - we're committed to helping you make the most of your bike touring experience. Join us in embracing this incredible lifestyle and start living the cycle touring life today!

 

What we offer
You will find the right gear at cycletouring.life whether for your daily commute, a family pedal to the park or beach, a weekend getaway, self-supported endurance event, a tour across the country or around the world. We have it all. 

We have reference material like books, and guides to help you prepare for the trip and know what it takes for the journey.  

Our range of top-quality products will make your bicycle tour what its meant to be: enjoyable, exciting and inspiring. We do not compromise on convenience, simplicity, durability and quality. We have all you need, such as Bike Panniers, bags, racks, to carry all you need during your adventure.  

The camping gear we have is lightweight and durable to make sure you are well-equipped to have the best experience possible on your of your tour. Our lightweight expedition tents, sleeping bags, stove and cooking wear for your journey will make sure your time off the saddle is unforgettable.  

Safety should always be the priority and incorporating this in your planning is a must. Being well equipped for any emergencies will make sure nothing gets in the way of the adventure you deserve. We have a wide range of survival gear that makes sure your journey remains one to remember.  

Remember that the adventure of a lifetime is out there, the world is waiting for you to discover it and the best way to do this in on your bike. 

So, what are you waiting for? Gear up and go!

ABOUT THE LILA NIKOLE COLLECTION

MADE WITH HEART
Lila Nikole Collection is a brand that promises to provide fresh, funky, styles constantly evolving and growing into your favorite swimwear brand. We use elements from everyday life like music, love, travels, and life experiences when designing our collection. Each design is infused with heart and designed to keep all of our beloved consumers in mind! We appreciate the love and support from all of you who chose us as your go to lifestyle brand.

The Lila Nikole Collection is a globally recognized swimwear and costume design brand, founded in 2010 by award-winning designer Lila Nikole Rivera. Based in the heart of Miami, the brand is known for delivering high-impact custom swimwear, and costumes that blend fashion, culture, and creativity. All designs, prototypes, and manufacturing are proudly produced in Miami, infused with the energy of the city’s vibrant, multicultural roots.

Lila Nikole's breakthrough into global acclaim stems from her standout work as the lead costume designer for the Super Bowl LV Halftime Show, where she styled the now-iconic performance by The Weeknd. Her Emmy-winning contributions also include costume design for Dr. Dre, Eminem, Mary J. Blige, Kendrick Lamar, and 50 Cent during the Super Bowl LVI Halftime Show. She has also designed custom looks for Imagine Dragons at the American Music Awards, and led wardrobe direction for the Kanye West Donda Tour. Lila created a standout look for DJ Spinderella at the GRAMMY Awards’ 50th Anniversary of Hip Hop Celebration, and extended her creativity into the sports world by designing custom F1 race uniforms for the Red Bull Racing Team.

Lila Nikole was proudly honored with induction into both the Rock & Roll Hall of Fame archives and the Hip Hop Museum, recognizing her groundbreaking contributions to music, fashion, and cultural expression through iconic costume and stage design. Over the years, the Lila Nikole Collection has been featured in major fashion publications including Vogue, Elle, GQ, Harper’s Bazaar, Sports Illustrated, and Cosmopolitan. The brand has styled a long list of celebrities and influencers such as Will Smith, Kim Kardashian, Serena Williams, Chrissy Teigen, Gigi Hadid, Jenny McCarthy, Keyshia Cole, Sara Underwood, and Amrezy, earning the title of celebrity-favorite swimwear designer.

Lila’s influence extends into the world of professional sports, having partnered with 10 NFL teams and 2 NBA teams to create custom cheerleader swimsuits, calendar features, and designs for HBO’s Hard Knocks: Miami Dolphins and NFL kickoff events. Her work has also appeared in numerous television productions, fashion shows, and media campaigns, including CNN Español, BET’s Rip the Runway, Fashion TV Best Swimwear, Univision’s Nuestra Belleza Latina, and the Sports Illustrated 50th Anniversary Swimsuit Issue.

From the runway to the football field, Lila Nikole’s creative impact spans multiple industries. Her journey from a solo designer to a globally respected name in fashion and costume design has even earned her recognition in academia—she was recently featured as a subject in a collegiate psychology textbook published by Feldman University, highlighting her entrepreneurial and artistic journey.

Beyond her success in fashion, Lila is deeply committed to giving back. The Lila Nikole Collection proudly supports numerous charitable causes and nonprofit organizations, including Project Save Imagination, Make-A-Wish Foundation, Boys & Girls Club of Miami, Food Bank for Hunger NYC, Chapman Partnership for Women and Children, Share Our Strength, and the Miami Dolphins Cystic Fibrosis Foundation. Her mission is not only to design with purpose but to uplift communities and empower future creatives through art and fashion.

About Us
Meet Dr. Thomas Jackson, D.D.S.
The Inventor Of The AutoFlosser

Dr. Thomas Jackson, D.D.S. has over 25 years of expertise in the dental field. He is a board-certified periodontist and founder of the Chicago Center for Cosmetic & Implant Dentistry. Dr. Jackson is a graduate of Northwestern University Dental School and completed his residency training at Johns Hopkins Hospital in Baltimore, Maryland. He also received specialty training at the University of Pennsylvania in periodontics and prosthodontics. 

Dr. Jackson has served as an associate professor at Northwestern University’s Feinberg School of Medicine. He is a frequent lecturer both nationally and internationally on cosmetics and dental implant topics and trends. Dr. Jackson has been featured on national television (WGN), as well as in the Chicago Tribune.

Dental Floss For Implants, Bridges, Braces & Bonded Retainers 

Dental professionals for more than a century have educated their patients about the critically important benefits that regular teeth flossing can provide for a lifetime of oral health.

For years, Dr. Jackson listened to his patients describe their struggles with flossing caused by solid or connected dental appliances, such as implants, bridges, crowns, braces and fixed retainers. Researching the existing marketplace for a specially designed flossing system to address these issues, Dr. Jackson was unable to find a satisfactory solution.

Hence, The AutoFlosser was born.

Dr. Jackson’s Autoflosser is a revolution in oral hygiene technology, designed for any person who cannot floss using traditional methods. The AutoFlosser is a sturdy, easy to hold device that allows users to point its tip at the exact place where they want to floss and then gently insert the floss thread via a simple turn of a wheel. The patient is then easily able to clean every area around the teeth and gumline.

In clinical tests, patients with connected appliance challenges have reported an extremely satisfying and refreshing flossing experience with Dr. Jackson’s Autoflosser.

Dr. Jackson has taken more than a quarter of a century of his direct professional experience and advanced training in periodontics and periodontal prosthesis to develop the Autoflosser. If you have trouble properly flossing due to the presence of a connected or solid dental appliance, The AutoFlosser is your solution.

Click here to learn more about how The AutoFlosser can restore the benefits, as well as that indescribable clean feeling back to your life that only regular flossing can bring.

World’s First Kids’ Tech Ecosystem myFirst is the world’s first kids’ tech ecosystem: Real tech for kids with fun devices, connected services and kid-safe social network to socialise, share and go anywhere, all safely connected with their friends and family. myFirst’s fun devices provide a secure and entertaining platform for children to socialize, share experiences, and explore the digital realm—all under the watchful eye of trusted friends and family. Designed for seamless interactions within circles of loved ones including parents and grandparents, friends, and family. No ads, no strangers; only real connections.  From a child’s very first phone to the first camera in their collection, embark on a journey of discovery, connection, and joy together as a family. Welcome to a world where kids come first, and technology is a trusted companion on their exciting path of exploration. Get social and join our safe, digital world for over 1 million kids, families, and friends.   DESIGNED FOR KIDS, CREATED FOR PARENTS - BY PARENTS! In 2017, the spark for myFirst ignited unexpectedly from a simple father-daughter moment. Our Founder & CEO G-Jay Yong found inspiration when his two-year-old daughter insisted on taking pictures with his Canon DSLR. Concerned about the weight of the 2kg camera, G-Jay set out to find a digital alternative that would match his daughter’s enthusiasm.  To his surprise, the market offered no suitable solution. It was from this realization that led G-Jay to establish and the myFirst Camera was swiftly introduced, marking the beginning of a tech journey designed specifically for children. Thus, Ru Faye received her first ever camera and the myFirst KidsTech ecosystem was born.  It was not long after the launch of myFirst Camera that myFirst became the #1 Kid’s Camera Brand in South Korea. Driven by a larger vision to be the first touchpoint for tech products in children’s lives, myFirst has since diversified its offerings. With nearly 10 device categories, including watchphones, cameras, earbuds, 3D pens, sketch boards, and headphones, myFirst products are now available in over 36 countries.  Since, G-Jay and our team of “Super Dads” continue to embrace the entrepreneurial spirit, coupled with a commitment to enhancing children’s interaction with technology, which has propelled myFirst into a global phenomenon. The need for their kids to engage more with new technology as the world is developing is more apparent than ever. The brand continues to thrive, connecting with families around the world and creating innovative, kid-friendly tech experiences for the next generation.   RuFaye (Product Manager) and G-Jay Yong (Founder) myFirst aims to enrich a child’s learning process by moulding experiences through fun and innovative gadgets. Designed as a gateway to a child’s educational journey, our products aspire to redefine and reinvent the learning experience for kids, whether they’re toddlers or teens. Ultimately, myFirst continues to prepare kids and teens to embrace the technological era as they are growing.  myFirst is now loved by parents everywhere and sold across the globe, including Singapore, Japan, Taiwan, Korea, Qatar, UAE, Malaysia, Vietnam, Thailand, Philippines, Sweden, Spain, Mexico, UK and the USA!  OUR MISSION BUILDING A TECH HAVEN FOR KIDS Protect our Children myFirst cultivates a community where kids can safely embrace and get introduced to technology before they get in touch with the challenges of the adult tech world, which is crucial in today’s age.  Parenting Made Easy Our dedicated team prioritizes the creation of high-quality, reliable, and functional products, addressing every concern parents have for their children. Offering a range of styles and options for each device, myFirst caters to diverse parenting styles, ensuring there’s a tailored solution for every need and every situation. myFirst places immense value on feedback from parents and children, committing to a continuous enhancement of our products.  Families Stay Connected with Peace of Mind Join us on the journey to align the building blocks for building big and creative minds! Our mission lies in our technology and platform to open up new experiences, conversations, and memories as your families all around the world.

ABOUT
My name is Cameron, I am a 23-year-old entrepreneur from Ontario, Canada. I recently graduated from Algonquin College for "Business Management & Entrepreneurship" in April of 2021. I ended up founding Smell My Thongs in December of 2020 when I was on my Christmas break. I originally wanted to make a business that brought a little smile to people's faces while still having some fun.

During my Christmas break, I ended up watching a lot of "Shark Tank" on Netflix. Upon binge-watching all the episodes I ended up stumbling across the "Potato Parcel" episode which got me interested in the prank niche. I heard of glitter bombs before and briefly heard of potato parcel on YouTube before even seeing the shark tank episode in December. I ended up spending a few days looking at what was out there on the internet and what space I could come and try my take on it.

I originally saw this "panty prank" idea on Etsy and thought I could do it but better. So I took what I learnt from college and applied it to this business and that's how it became the success it is today. If you would like to see more behind the scenes of the business check out my tik tok!

About AndoAndoAndo
I love the word inclusivity. Why? Because I always felt like I was excluded.
"Men's" watches in the world that are so big, you can't wear. "Women's" watches in the world that's so small you can't see what time it is.

I wanted to make something genderless, ageless, and fun. So here we are, AndoAndoAndo.

It's not that we have products that everyone can enjoy. But we wanted to fill the holes in the watch industry to make the whole industry inclusive. A mid-sized watch for small-wristed men and mid-sized-wristed women to enjoy, a clock/watch that you don't need a hand to wear/carry, beautiful crystal decorated dials for anyone who enjoy crystals.
And of course, where is the fun in life if we don't have fun, interesting, quirky things to enjoy? That's who we are, AndoAndoAndo.

As most origin stories, my journey to creating Soul Spheres and launching the KeepingSpirit blog wasn't a linear one. Punctuated by a free spiritual upbringing, a life-changing thesis project and a far-too-close-to-death experience, I'm here to share my story.

My Origin Story
I grew up with parents that were never religious, but always spiritual. In great part they left me to discover my own truths about spirit, God, self and the meaning of life. I've always been fascinated by these subjects and have had a great desire, like I know many do, to understand the "truth" behind what happens after we die (and where were we before!?).

When I've experienced loss, whether it be one of my precious pets or the truly earth rattling loss of my Grandparents as a young teen, I always felt I could sense that they weren't really gone despite it hurting so deeply. So as I grew up, I explored these concepts in many different ways...sometimes through my own internal process, and sometimes in ways that were much more open to the world.

The Birth of Soul Spheres
In my senior year of college as a BFA candidate in Fine Jewelry, I pulled on this concept - "why are we who we are?" and answered with three different options:
1) We are souls that are also an expression of our physiology making this human experience a truly unique one - for this I made a helmet that screwed into pressure points that could affect our well being and seemily change our personalities

2) We are who we are 100% because of our physiology - for this I created a life-size spine necklace out of bronze that was worn down the back

3) We are who we are 100% because of our soul - for this I created Soul Spheres that each weighed 21 grams based off of the research of Dr. Duncan MacDougall

While from my own perspective I believe we are likely who we are as a result of a combination of some "spirit" and the physiology of our bodies, it was the Soul Spheres that really resonated with people. Although MacDougalls research was not necessarily sound, the concept of being able to connect with the weight of the soul - something truly physical beyond our bodies - was really touching to so many, myself included.

When Life Gets In the Way
As I left college, I grew my jewelry line for a few years but ultimately dropped it as life got busy and I pursued other things. I intended to come back to it all, but 10 years flies by fast!

Although I wasn't actively pursuing the thought of soul versus physiology during that time, I was on a long journey of self-care discovery and coming into my own during my 20s. I discovered many amazing tools and learned so much from some great teachers - some of these things include EFT, hypnosis, truths about anxiety etc.

Unconscious for 24 Hours
Then two years ago, I almost died from an acute case of Hyponatremia. It was incredibly scary experience for my family and for me, although I was in a coma for most of it and luckily don't remember the main part of the trauma. What I do remember though is that I don't recall anything from the coma. And that terrified me.

Rebirth of Soul Sphere and the Birth of KeepingSpirit
The experience has peeled a whole new layer away for me to explore - a refocusing on the existence of "life" after death by restarting my jewelry line with the Soul Spheres, but most importantly, focusing on how to make the most of the beautiful opportunities in front of us in this current life! 

So, that's what brought me to also establishing the KeepingSpirit blog/podcast/community alongside Soul Spheres - to connect & share on everything I've learned, and to learn from others invested in our well-being and Keeping a Spirited perspective to life!

I hope you'll join me by signing up below and introduce yourself!

About Us
Panic 39 Streetwear: Amplifying Underground Voices Through Style.
From its birth in Southern California to its now Global presence, Panic 39 Streetwear has been a staple in the Underground Scene’s since 1999.  Panic 39 embodies the very essence of rebellious self-expression. Worn proudly by, B-Boys, B-Girls, Poppers, Lockers, Streetdancers, Junglists, Underground Hip Hop Heads, Extreme Athletes, Skaters, Fighters, House Heads and Streetwear Enthusiast, Panic 39 isn't merely a clothing company; it's a testament to the rebellious spirit and authentic expression that define underground subcultures. 

The Birth of an Icon: From the depths of the underground, Panic 39 Streetwear was conceived as a tribute to the voices that echoed through the alleyways, the artists who painted stories on the walls, The Emcees and DJ’s who laid the soundtrack and the dancers who found freedom in movement. Rooted in the very fabric of these subcultures, our brand serves as an emblem of rebellion against conformity.

Wearing the Stories: Forthe Underground, clothing is a means of communication. Panic 39 Streetwear is a wearable canvas, a vivid representation of their journeys and passions. Our designs capture iconic street dance moves, graffiti art, and the pulsating beats of Hip- Hop, Drum 'n' Bass and House Music, infusing clothing with the heartbeat of the streets.

Uniting the Underground: Beyond clothing, Panic 39 Streetwear stands as a unifying force. We're more than a brand; we're a community bound by the love for dance, music, art, and the spirit of the streets. Collaborations, events, and platforms echo our commitment to fostering connections and inspiring creativity within our tribe.

Join the Movement: Panic 39 Streetwear extends an invitation to all urban warriors, dance pioneers, graffiti artists, and those who forge their paths. Whether you're moving to the rhythms of the Underground or making your mark on city walls, let Panic 39 be your badge of authenticity and your symbol of solidarity.

Elevate the Beat. Elevate the Culture. Elevate Yourself.

We are The Sardar Co...
a brand built on integrity,
pride, and independence.
What does “sardar” mean to us? It means strength of character, independence, a sense of identity and purpose. Sardars know who they are, and they’re not afraid to show it to the world. They come from all cultures and all walks of life, sharing a common identity of self-respect and independence. We’re proud to welcome you as one sardar to another, no matter what your cultural heritage, background, gender or age.

Building a brand for sardars
We’re Manny and Manjit, the children of first and second-generation immigrants. We grew up Sikh in a non-Sikh neighbourhood, knowing that we were different and often feeling out of place. At school, in the workplace, and in day-to-day life, people saw us differently because of the way we looked and the culture we came from.

Being different can be isolating. But difference can also mean independence, pride, and a sense of true identity. It’s okay to stand
out from the crowd, to be true to yourself instead of what others want you to be. We’re proud to be different, to lead rather than to follow; to be sardars.

What do we want to achieve?
Being at peace with who you are is the foundation of the Sardar Co. We don’t go for flash-in-the-pan fads or gimmicks. Our vision is to offer styling products that complement your individual style, instead of replacing it. To enhance your identity, instead of dressing it up. We’ll help you to show the world the truest possible version of yourself.

ABOUT US

I'M FABULOUS® was founded and created by Anis, a licensed aesthetician with a medical background and over 20 years of experience working with burn survivors and cancer patients. In her quest to develop world-class skincare products that are effective and not just off-the-shelf creams, she has collaborated with chemists, plastic surgeons, cancer patients, and burn survivors. Anis has studied plant botany and phytotherapy. She has explored alternative forms of healing through studies in anatomy, Ayurveda, traditional Chinese medicine, and yoga. With several years of experience in anti-aging care, skin correction, and microdermabrasion, she developed the I'M FABULOUS® anti-aging and skin correction products at the beginning of 2004. Throughout our lives, we all experience occasional sunburns, regular sun exposure, hormonal changes, stress, and environmental pollution. All these factors contribute to the signs of premature aging. This group of therapeutic systems for the skin has been formulated to improve the signs of aging at the cellular level by:

Improving skin cell function  
Minimizing signs of premature aging  
Reducing future photo damage  
Helping the skin appear and act younger and healthier  
Reducing acne breakouts  
Reducing hyperpigmentation   As your skin ages and is exposed to UVA and UVB rays, the renewal of skin cells significantly slows down, disrupting the balance between the growth of new healthy cells and the shedding of old and damaged cells. Additionally, collagen and elastin begin to break down, leading to a loss of skin elasticity, resulting in fine lines, wrinkles, and sagging. Daily exposure to UV rays then accelerates this aging process and can cause uneven skin tone. Our range of therapeutic skincare formulas works to restore the lost skin integrity as quickly as possible.

The signs of photodamage that these products reverse are:

Age spots  
Wrinkles and fine lines  
Rough skin  
Skin laxity  
Erythema (redness)  
Superficiality (complexion)  
Hyperpigmentation (discoloration)
